## 4. Proposed upstream artifacts

For each repo, two artifacts.

### 4.1 Triage Issue

**Title:** `[provider] ClinePass — track first-class support`

**Body outline (both repos):**

1. **What ClinePass is** — link to `https://cline.bot/cline-pass`, list the
   10 models and 6 labs (from the public page), state the launch terms
   (`$4.99` → `$9.99/mo`).
2. **Why it fits this project's wiring** — for forgecode: explain how
   `ProviderResponse::OpenAI` plus `provider.json` makes new OpenAI-compat
   providers a JSON-only change; for omniroute: explain the
   `apikey/gateways.ts` + `registry/<id>/index.ts` pairing and the
   `check-provider-consistency.ts` gate.
3. **Open questions** (per repo, identical five):
   - (i) Base URL.
   - (ii) API key issuance surface and env-var name.
   - (iii) Wire protocol (OpenAI-compat / Responses / Anthropic-compat).
   - (iv) Model-id namespace at the ClinePass provider.
   - (v) Whether Cline IDE/CLI keys are interchangeable with third-party-agent keys.
4. **Linkage** — track the eventual PR here; PR will link back.

### 4.2 Draft PR (after Issue feedback, default mode)

**`tailcallhq/forgecode`** — touches at most four files:

- `crates/forge_domain/src/provider.rs:46-128,176-222` — `ProviderId::CLINEPASS`
  const + `display_name` arm + `FromStr` arm.
- `crates/forge_repo/src/provider/provider.json` — single JSON entry block
  (id, `api_key_vars: ["CLINEPASS_API_KEY"]`, `response_type: "OpenAI"`,
  `url`, `models`, `auth_methods`). **Default value of `url` is a clearly
  marked `<pending-ClinePass-endpoint>` placeholder until (i) is answered.**
- `crates/forge_domain/src/provider.rs:` —
  `test_cline_pass_from_str`, `test_cline_pass_display_name`,
  `test_cline_pass_in_built_in_providers`, mirroring the
  `fireworks-ai-firepass` precedent.
- Optionally `crates/forge_repo/src/provider/provider_repo.rs` — a
  `test_cline_pass_config` mirroring `test_openai_compatible_config`.

**`diegosouzapw/omniroute`** — touches at most five files:

- `src/shared/constants/providers/apikey/gateways.ts` — add a new
  `clinepass` entry alongside `crof`, `openadapter`, etc.
- `open-sse/config/providers/registry/clinepass/index.ts` — **new file**
  shaped like `crof/index.ts:1-38`. Same `<pending-ClinePass-endpoint>`
  placeholder default until (i) is answered.
- `open-sse/config/providers/index.ts:172,343` — append the new import line
  and add `clinepass: clinepassProvider,` to `REGISTRY`.
- Optionally `public/providers/clinepass.svg` — only if a logo exists (no
  required default).
- Optionally `docs/providers/CLINEPASS.md` — only if the project treats
  per-provider docs as required (template at `docs/providers/AGENTROUTER.md`).

PRs are to be opened as **Drafts** by default — the maintainer-facing signal
that the diff is reviewable but explicitly not finished until the five open
questions are answered.

---

## 5. Execution authority and gate

Opening Issues on org-owned upstream repos and pushing branches to your forks
that open PRs against those org-owned repos are *external actions* whose
blast radius is global (notifications, public essay-style PR discussion, etc.)
and somewhat irreversible (closed issues/PRs remain visible).

This design spec therefore names two gating questions whose answers must come
from the user before any `gh issue create --repo <upstream>` or
`gh pr create --repo <upstream>` is called:

1. **Draft mode vs delete-later** — recommendation: open Issues as **real
   Issues**; open PRs as **Drafts**. Confirm, or specify other.
2. **Auth-app credentialed fetch** — recommendation: **(a)** sign in to
   `app.cline.bot`, let the agent fetch unauthenticated sub-resources to
   triangulate the real base URL + env-var name + transport, then draft Issues
   and PRs from confirmed facts. Alternative: **(b)** ship Issues with the
   open-questions section populated and let upstream maintainers answer in
   thread; iterate PR after.

Until both have a confirmed answer, the upstream execution steps remain
explicitly **BACKLOG — blocked on user authorization**.

