## 7. Open-question tracking table

Tracked explicitly so the design does not drift from the spec.

| # | Question | Source of eventual answer | Default in PR diff until answered? |
|---|----------|----------------------------|-----------------------------------:|
| 1 | ClinePass base URL                | `app.cline.bot` after auth ok | Yes — `<pending-ClinePass-endpoint>` |
| 2 | API key env-var name              | upstream docs / `app.cline.bot` API-keys page | Yes — `CLINEPASS_API_KEY` |
| 3 | Wire protocol (compat shape)      | inspection of first response to (1)+(2) | Yes — OpenAI-compat (most permissive) |
| 4 | Model-id namespace                | "models" listing on the provider | Yes — passthrough where possible |
| 5 | Interchangeability IDE-key vs agent-key | `app.cline.bot` agent-key settings | Yes — assume separation, document it |

---

## 8. Failure modes

- **Failure A — base URL is not OpenAI-compat:** the forgecode `OpenAI` routing
  assumption fails. Effort climbs MEDIUM-HIGH in forgecode (new
  `ProviderResponse` variant + `*ResponseRepository`). The Issue's
  open-questions section surfaces this so it is caught before code review
  starts.
- **Failure B — `check-provider-consistency.ts` flags the omniroute entry:**
  the dual-source covenant between catalog and registry is unfixable from a
  single PR; the PR will fail CI locally before it is pushed. Mitigation: the
  PR opens both files together in one commit.
- **Failure C — Cline Inc. patents/trademark objections to provider id
  `cline_pass`:** reroute id to a non-trademark namespace (`cp_*` or
  `clinepass` unhyphenated per omniroute's existing `cline` OAuth entry);
  the open-questions section gives maintainers a chance to surface this
  *before* code lands.

---

